        {
          "sentences": [
            {
              "text": "In the balanced budget for the 2019–20 fiscal year, worth $40 billion, the State of Illinois authorized more spending on education, including grade schools, community colleges, and state universities."
            },
            {
              "text": "Funding for grade schools rose by nearly $379 million, more than the $29 million required by the new state funding for education formula passed the previous year."
            },
            {
              "text": "Funding for community colleges increased by $14 million, for public universities by $53 million."
            },
            {
              "text": "Grants for low-income students received a $50 million bump."
            },
            {
              "text": "The Illinois Department of Children and Family Services, facing financial pressure, received $80 million for hiring new staff and improving services."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "sentences": [
            {
              "text": "On top of that, the Rebuild Illinois capital plan spent some $3.2 billion for public colleges and universities over six years."
